@startuml
!pragma plantuml_limit_size 8192
title Personal Budgeting System - Class Diagram
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam monochrome true
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowColor #555555
skinparam ClassBorderColor #333333

' ===================== View Layer (accounts app) =====================
package "accounts (Auth Views)" as LayerAuth {
    class signup_view <<view>> {
        + GET(): render signup page
        + POST(): register user (JSON or form)
    }
    class login_view <<view>> {
        + GET(): render login page
        + POST(): authenticate(); login(request, user)
    }
    class logout_view <<view>> {
        + POST(): logout(request); redirect login
    }
}

note bottom of login_view
  **Sequence diagrams** may show **AuthService**
  (login / validateCredentials).
  In Spendo this is implemented inside **login_view**
  using Django **authenticate()** and **login()** —
  there is no separate AuthService class.
end note

note right of signup_view
  **POST** uses **User.objects.filter**(…)**.exists()**,
  **User.objects.create_user**, **user.save**
end note

' ===================== View Layer (dashboard app) =====================
package "dashboard (Dashboard Views)" as LayerDashboard {
    class getDashboard <<view>> {
        + GET(): KPIs, charts, budget overview, alerts
    }
    class getNotifications <<view>> {
        + GET(): list notifications for user
    }
}

note right of getDashboard
  **Transaction.objects.filter** / aggregates,
  **Category.objects.filter**,
  **Notification.objects.filter** + **.create**
  (deduped budget / upcoming alerts)
end note

note right of getNotifications
  **Notification.objects.filter**(user)**.order_by**(…)
end note

' ===================== View Layer (finances app) =====================
package "finances (Finance Views)" as LayerFinances {
    class CategoryViews <<view module>> {
        + add_category(request): POST
        + delete_category(request, category_id): POST
    }
    class BudgetViews <<view module>> {
        + set_budget(request): POST (JSON)
        + get_budget_page(request): GET
    }
    class TransactionViews <<view module>> {
        + add_transaction(request): POST
        + update_transaction(request, transaction_id): POST
        + delete_transaction(request, transaction_id): POST
        + get_transactions_page(request): GET + filter
    }
    class ReportViews <<view module>> {
        + get_reports_page(request): GET + period
        + dashboard_data(request): GET (JSON)
    }
}

note right of CategoryViews
  **Category.objects.get_or_create**, **.save**,
  **Notification.objects.create**
end note

note right of BudgetViews
  **set_budget**: **Category.objects.get**,
  **Budget.objects.update_or_create**
  **get_budget_page**: **Category.objects.filter**,
  **Transaction.objects.filter** + **Sum**
end note

note right of TransactionViews
  **add_transaction**: **Category.get_or_create**,
  **Transaction.objects.create**,
  **Notification.objects.create**;
  **post_save** → **checkBudgetAmount**
end note

note right of ReportViews
  **Transaction** / **Category** queries and aggregates;
  **dashboard_data** also reads **Goal**
end note

' ===================== View Layer (goals app) =====================
package "goals (Goal Views)" as LayerGoals {
    class GoalFunctionViews <<view module>> {
        + getGoals(request): GET
        + getGoal(request, goalId): GET
        + add_goal(request): POST
        + delete_goal(request, goal_id): POST
        + depositGoalAmount(request): POST / PUT (JSON)
    }
    class GoalCreateView <<CreateView>> {
        + model: Goal
        + fields: list
        + template_name: string
        + success_url: string
        + form_valid(form)
    }
    class GoalUpdateView <<UpdateView>> {
        + model: Goal
        + fields: list
        + template_name: string
        + success_url: string
        + slug_field: string
        + slug_url_kwarg: string
        + form_valid(form)
    }
}

note right of GoalFunctionViews
  **Goal.objects.create** / **.get** / **.save**;
  **Notification.objects.create** on add/update/delete goal
  (**depositGoalAmount** updates **current** only)
end note

' ===================== Models (Entity Layer) =====================
package "Models (Entity Layer)" as LayerModel {

    class User <<Django Built-in>> {
        - id: int
        - username: string
        - email: string
        - password: string
        - first_name: string
        - is_staff: bool
        __manager (objects)__
        + filter(**kwargs): QuerySet
        + create_user(username, password, **extra): User
        + save(): void
    }

    class Category <<Model>> {
        - id: int
        - name: string
        - budgeted: Decimal
        - spent: Decimal
        - icon: string
        - is_custom: bool
        __manager__
        + filter(**kwargs): QuerySet
        + get(**kwargs): Category
        + get_or_create(defaults, **kwargs): Category
        + save(): void
    }

    class Budget <<Model>> {
        - id: int
        - amount: Decimal
        - start_date: Date
        - end_date: Date
        - alert_threshold: int
        __manager__
        + filter(**kwargs): QuerySet
        + update_or_create(defaults, **kwargs): Budget
    }

    class Transaction <<Model>> {
        - id: int
        - name: string
        - amount: Decimal
        - type: string <<income|expense>>
        - date: DateTime
        - payment_method: string
        - description: string
        - is_upcoming: bool
        - due_date: Date
        __manager__
        + filter(**kwargs): QuerySet
        + create(**kwargs): Transaction
        + save(): void
    }

    class Notification <<Model>> {
        - id: int
        - message: string
        - reference_key: string
        - alert_type: string <<general|budget|upcoming>>
        - is_read: bool
        - created_at: DateTime
        __manager__
        + filter(**kwargs): QuerySet
        + create(**kwargs): Notification
    }

    class Goal <<Model>> {
        - id: UUID
        - name: string
        - description: string
        - dueDate: Date
        - target: Decimal
        - current: Decimal
        - image: ImageField
        - createdAt: DateTime
        - updatedAt: DateTime
        + getProgress(): float
        __manager__
        + filter(**kwargs): QuerySet
        + get(**kwargs): Goal
        + create(**kwargs): Goal
        + save(): void
    }

    class checkBudgetAmount <<signal receiver>> {
        + handler(sender, instance, created, **kwargs): void
    }
}

note bottom of checkBudgetAmount
  **@receiver(post_save, sender=Transaction)** — **finances/signals.py**
  **Budget.objects.filter**(…)**.first()**,
  **Transaction.objects.filter**(…)**.aggregate(Sum)**,
  **Notification.objects.create**
end note

' ===================== Layout hints =====================
LayerAuth -[hidden]right-> LayerDashboard
LayerDashboard -[hidden]right-> LayerFinances
LayerFinances -[hidden]right-> LayerGoals
LayerAuth -[hidden]down-> LayerModel
LayerDashboard -[hidden]down-> LayerModel
LayerFinances -[hidden]down-> LayerModel
LayerGoals -[hidden]down-> LayerModel

' ===================== View → Model Dependencies =====================

signup_view ..> User
login_view ..> User

getDashboard ..> Transaction
getDashboard ..> Category
getDashboard ..> Notification
getNotifications ..> Notification

CategoryViews ..> Category
CategoryViews ..> Notification
BudgetViews ..> Budget
BudgetViews ..> Category
BudgetViews ..> Transaction
TransactionViews ..> Transaction
TransactionViews ..> Category
TransactionViews ..> Notification
ReportViews ..> Transaction
ReportViews ..> Category
ReportViews ..> Goal

GoalFunctionViews ..> Goal
GoalFunctionViews ..> Notification
GoalCreateView ..> Goal
GoalUpdateView ..> Goal

' ===================== Signal =====================
checkBudgetAmount ..> Transaction : post_save
checkBudgetAmount ..> Budget : reads
checkBudgetAmount ..> Notification : creates
TransactionViews ..> checkBudgetAmount : after save

' ===================== Model FK Associations =====================
User "1" o-- "0..*" Transaction : owns
User "1" o-- "0..*" Category : owns
User "1" o-- "0..*" Budget : owns
User "1" o-- "0..*" Goal : authors
User "1" o-- "0..*" Notification : receives

Transaction "0..*" --> "0..1" Category : categorized by
Budget "0..*" --> "1" Category : limits
Budget "0..*" --> "1" User : owned by

@enduml
